    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-02T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-02T09:00:00-05:00" n="333"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/5–251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DAC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d333fn1">Repeated for information to Amman and
                        Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-02T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 2, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>696. <persName corresp="#p_SR2">Shiloah</persName> told us he has had recent
                    conference with <persName corresp="#p_KCDB1">King</persName> Abdullah at
                    latter’s request to discuss Israel reply to <gloss target="#t_PriMin1"
                        >PriMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_ARS1">Samir</persName> Kifai’s written proposal (see
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 667 Apr 20).<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d333fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_647">p. 647</ref>.</note> When
                        <persName corresp="#p_SR2">Shiloah</persName> enquired whether the <persName
                        corresp="#p_KCDB1">King</persName> wished to have <persName
                        corresp="#p_ARS1">Samir</persName> present, Abdullah replied he preferred
                    speak to him alone since he was displeased with both <persName corresp="#p_ARS1"
                        >Samir</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SR2">Shiloah</persName> over
                    exchange of correspondence. He deplored raising sovereignty issue and Israel’s
                    undiplomatic rejoinder saying he wondered whether both govts might not withdraw
                    their respective communications. <persName corresp="#p_SR2">Shiloah</persName>
                    replied that altho such withdrawal wld present some practical difficulties he
                    believed it might nevertheless <pb facs="0697" n="657" xml:id="pg_657"/> be
                    done. The <persName corresp="#p_KCDB1">King</persName> then suggested Israelis
                    disregard any intemperance in Jordan’s reply and consider possibility of
                    withdrawing entire correspondence. <persName corresp="#p_SR2">Shiloah</persName>
                    thereupon spoke of possibility that Israel might be prepared release some
                    blocked balances in order to create more favorable atmosphere. He says <persName
                        corresp="#p_KCDB1">King</persName> Abdullah showed lively interest in this
                    prospect and seemed hopeful it might serve useful purpose. In this connection
                    however <persName corresp="#p_SR2">Shiloah</persName> remarked that while he
                    believes Abdullah means well and has good ideas, he has now become “wishful
                    thinker” and is believed to lack real power to implement views which are his
                    alone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
